00019 void *eol_resource_manager_load_resource(eolResourceManager *manager,char *filename)
00020 {
00021   eolResourceHeader * element = NULL;
00022   if (!filename)return NULL;
00023   if (manager->data_load == NULL)
00024   {
00025     return NULL;
00026   }
00027   if (manager->_data_unique == eolFalse)
00028   {
00029     element = eol_resource_find_element_by_filename(manager,filename);
00030     if (element != NULL)
00031     {
00032       if (element->refCount == 0)
00033       {
00034         manager->_data_count++;
00035       }
00036       element->refCount++;
00037       return eol_resource_get_data_by_header(element);
00038     }
00039   }
00040   element = eol_resource_get_header_by_data(eol_resource_new_element(manager));
00041   if (element == NULL)
00042   {
00043     return NULL;
00044   }
00045   
00046   if (manager->data_load != NULL)
00047   {
00048     if (!manager->data_load(filename,eol_resource_get_data_by_header(element)))
00049     {
00050       eol_resource_delete_element(manager,element);
00051       return NULL;
00052     }
00053   }
00054   eol_line_cpy(element->filename,filename);
00055   return eol_resource_get_data_by_header(element);

00527 eolBool eol_resource_validate_header_range(eolResourceManager *manager,eolResourceHeader *element)
00528 {
00529   if (!manager)return eolFalse;
00530   if (!element)return eolFalse;
00531   if ((void *)element < (void *)manager->_data_list)
00532   {
00533     eol_logger_message(

00535       "eol_resource: underseeking in data list.\n");

00537   }

00539   {
